  <h2>How to Use This Calculator</h2>

  <h3>Investment Growth tab</h3>
  <p>The default tab. Enter your <strong>initial deposit</strong> and <strong>monthly contribution</strong> — the calculator shows your total balance after compound interest. Expand <strong>"More options"</strong> to adjust the interest rate, compounding frequency, and time period. The default rate reflects a long-term stock market average. For savings accounts, lower it to 3–5%.</p>

  <h3>Savings Goal tab</h3>
